         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/2/62 ¶ Dear Sir William. ¶  ¶ I have much pleasure of sending you a copy of invoice of a few articles, which I have forwarded pr. " ¶ True Britain ¶ " ¶  to the International Exhibition. ¶  You wil...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.02.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' letters, vol. LXXV, Australian and Pacific letters 1859-65, letter no. 144.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black edged; M's sister Bertha died on 7 September 1861.</p>
               </note>12/2/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir William.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have much pleasure of sending you a copy of invoice of a few articles, which I have forwarded pr. "<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">True Britain</hi>
               </seg>"<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i. e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">True Briton</seg>, which cleared out of Hobson's Bay for London on 17 February (Argus, 18 February 1862, p. 4)<seg style="font-style: italic; ">. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note> to the International Exhibition.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Invoice and list of articles not found.</p>
               </note> You will perceive, that this brings up the timber specimens to 463 pieces. With exception of about a dozend, sent with others pr. Great Britain, and which are intended for fittings, it is my desire that not only all these timbers but also the other vegetable products <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in toto</hi>
               </seg> should be placed at your disposal for deposition in Kew after the close of the Exhibition</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever highly regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
   </text>
